Analyze the search results data (COMPLETELY FIXED VERSION) if json_data and 'results' in json_data: print(f'\n📊 ANALYZING {len(json_data["results"])} SEARCH RESULTS FOR MAYA ALI BIRTH INFORMATION:') print('=' * 80) # Initialize analysis results birth_analysis = { 'analysis_timestamp': '2025-01-07', 'total_results_analyzed': len(json_data['results']), 'birth_year_evidence': [], 'birth_date_evidence': [], 'source_reliability': {}, 'consensus_findings': {}, 'conflicting_information': [] } # Extract all birth-related information all_birth_indicators = [] all_years_mentioned = [] all_dates_mentioned = [] reliable_sources = [] print('\n🔍 PROCESSING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BIRTH INFORMATION:') print('-' * 60) # Define reliable domains for source verification reliable_domains = ['wikipedia.org', 'imdb.com', 'famousbirthdays.com', 'starsunfolded.com', 'themoviedb.org', 'hamariweb.com'] for i, result in enumerate(json_data['results'], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') body = result.get('body', 'No body') link = result.get('link', result.get('href', 'No link')) relevance_score = result.get('relevance_score', 0) birth_indicators = result.get('birth_indicators', []) years_mentioned = result.get('years_mentioned', []) dates_mentioned = result.get('dates_mentioned', []) print(f'\nResult {i}: Score {relevance_score}') print(f' Title: {title[:100]}...') print(f' Birth indicators: {birth_indicators[:3]}...' if len(birth_indicators) > 3 else f' Birth indicators: {birth_indicators}') print(f' Years: {years_mentioned} | Dates: {dates_mentioned}') print(f' Link: {link[:80]}...') # Collect all evidence all_birth_indicators.extend(birth_indicators) all_years_mentioned.extend(years_mentioned) all_dates_mentioned.extend(dates_mentioned) # Check if source is reliable (FIXED: no generator expression scoping issues) is_reliable = False for domain in reliable_domains: if domain in link.lower(): is_reliable = True break if is_reliable and (birth_indicators or (relevance_score >= 20 and years_mentioned)): reliable_sources.append({ 'title': title, 'link': link, 'score': relevance_score, 'birth_indicators': birth_indicators, 'years': years_mentioned, 'dates': dates_mentioned, 'body': body[:300] }) print(f' ✅ RELIABLE SOURCE IDENTIFIED') # Store detailed evidence if birth_indicators or years_mentioned or dates_mentioned: birth_analysis['birth_year_evidence'].append({ 'source': title[:100], 'link': link, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'birth_indicators': birth_indicators, 'years_mentioned': years_mentioned, 'dates_mentioned': dates_mentioned, 'is_reliable_source': is_reliable }) # Analyze patterns in the evidence print('\n' + '=' * 80) print('COMPREHENSIVE BIRTH INFORMATION ANALYSIS') print('=' * 80) # Count frequency of birth indicators birth_indicator_counts = Counter(all_birth_indicators) year_counts = Counter(all_years_mentioned) date_counts = Counter(all_dates_mentioned) print(f'\n📊 BIRTH EVIDENCE FREQUENCY ANALYSIS:') print(f' • Total birth indicators found: {len(all_birth_indicators)}') print(f' • Unique birth indicators: {len(set(all_birth_indicators))}') print(f' • Total years mentioned: {len(all_years_mentioned)}') print(f' • Unique years mentioned: {len(set(all_years_mentioned))}') print(f' • Total dates mentioned: {len(all_dates_mentioned)}') print(f' • Unique dates mentioned: {len(set(all_dates_mentioned))}') print(f' • Reliable sources identified: {len(reliable_sources)}') # Show most common birth indicators if birth_indicator_counts: print(f'\n💡 MOST COMMON BIRTH INDICATORS:') for indicator, count in birth_indicator_counts.most_common(10): print(f' • {indicator}: {count} occurrences') # Show most common years if year_counts: print(f'\n📅 MOST COMMON YEARS MENTIONED:') for year, count in year_counts.most_common(10): print(f' • {year}: {count} occurrences') # Show most common dates if date_counts: print(f'\n📆 MOST COMMON DATES/MONTHS MENTIONED:') for date, count in date_counts.most_common(10): print(f' • {date}: {count} occurrences') # Focus on reliable sources print(f'\n🏆 ANALYSIS OF RELIABLE SOURCES ({len(reliable_sources)}):') print('-' * 60) if reliable_sources: # Sort reliable sources by relevance score reliable_sources.sort(key=lambda x: x['score'], reverse=True) for i, source in enumerate(reliable_sources, 1): print(f'\n{i}. Extract consensus from reliable sources reliable_years = [] reliable_dates = [] reliable_indicators = [] for source in reliable_sources: reliable_years.extend(source['years']) reliable_dates.extend(source['dates']) reliable_indicators.extend(source['birth_indicators']) reliable_year_counts = Counter(reliable_years) reliable_date_counts = Counter(reliable_dates) reliable_indicator_counts = Counter(reliable_indicators) print(f'\n🎯 CONSENSUS FROM RELIABLE SOURCES:') if reliable_year_counts: most_common_year = reliable_year_counts.most_common(1)[0] print(f' Most common birth year: {most_common_year[0]} ({most_common_year[1]} reliable sources)') birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['most_likely_birth_year'] = most_common_year[0] birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['birth_year_confidence'] = most_common_year[1] if reliable_date_counts: most_common_date = reliable_date_counts.most_common(1)[0] print(f' Most common birth date element: {most_common_date[0]} ({most_common_date[1]} reliable sources)') birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['most_likely_date_element'] = most_common_date[0] if reliable_indicator_counts: print(f' Most reliable birth indicators:') for indicator, count in reliable_indicator_counts.most_common(5): print(f' • {indicator} ({count} reliable sources)') # Look for specific birth date patterns in reliable sources print(f'\n🔍 EXTRACTING SPECIFIC BIRTH DATES FROM RELIABLE SOURCES:') birth_date_patterns = [] for source in reliable_sources: content = f"{source['title']} {source['body']}".lower() # Look for specific date patterns # Pattern: July 27, 1989 or 27 July 1989 date_pattern1 = re.findall(r'(july|jul)\s+(27|27th),?\s+(1989|1988)', content) date_pattern2 = re.findall(r'(27|27th)\s+(july|jul)\s+(1989|1988)', content) date_pattern3 = re.findall(r'(1989|1988)[-/](07|7)[-/](27)', content) for pattern in date_pattern1: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"{pattern[1]} {pattern[0]} {pattern[2]}") for pattern in date_pattern2: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"{pattern[0]} {pattern[1]} {pattern[2]}") for pattern in date_pattern3: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"27 July {pattern[0]}") if birth_date_patterns: date_pattern_counts = Counter(birth_date_patterns) print(f' Specific birth date patterns found:') for pattern, count in date_pattern_counts.most_common(5): print(f' • {pattern} ({count} reliable sources)') if date_pattern_counts: most_likely_date = date_pattern_counts.most_common(1)[0] birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['most_likely_full_birth_date'] = most_likely_date[0] birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['birth_date_confidence'] = most_likely_date[1] print(f'\n🏆 MOST LIKELY BIRTH DATE: {most_likely_date[0]} (from {most_likely_date[1]} reliable sources)') else: print('❌ No reliable sources found with birth information') # Calculate overall confidence score confidence_score = 0 if len(reliable_sources) > 0: confidence_score += 30 if len(reliable_sources) >= 3: confidence_score += 20 if birth_indicator_counts: confidence_score += 20 if year_counts and len(set(all_years_mentioned)) <= 3: confidence_score += 15 # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_file = os.path.join(workspace_dir, 'maya_ali_birth_analysis_final.json') with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(birth_analysis, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n💾 COMPREHENSIVE BIRTH ANALYSIS SAVED TO: {analysis_file}') # Look for specific birth date patterns in reliable sources print(f'\n🔍 EXTRACTING SPECIFIC BIRTH DATES FROM RELIABLE SOURCES:') birth_date_patterns = [] for source in reliable_sources: content = f"{source['title']} {source['body']}".lower() # Look for specific date patterns # Pattern: July 27, 1989 or 27 July 1989 date_pattern1 = re.findall(r'(july|jul)\s+(27|27th),?\s+(1989|1988)', content) date_pattern2 = re.findall(r'(27|27th)\s+(july|jul)\s+(1989|1988)', content) date_pattern3 = re.findall(r'(1989|1988)[-/](07|7)[-/](27)', content) for pattern in date_pattern1: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"{pattern[1]} {pattern[0]} {pattern[2]}") for pattern in date_pattern2: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"{pattern[0]} {pattern[1]} {pattern[2]}") for pattern in date_pattern3: if pattern: birth_date_patterns.append(f"27 July {pattern[0]}") if birth_date_patterns: date_pattern_counts = Counter(birth_date_patterns) print(f' Specific birth date patterns found:') for pattern, count in date_pattern_counts.most_common(5): print(f' • {pattern} ({count} reliable sources)') if date_pattern_counts: most_likely_date = date_pattern_counts.most_common(1)[0] birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['most_likely_full_birth_date'] = most_likely_date[0] birth_analysis['consensus_findings']['birth_date_confidence'] = most_likely_date[1] print(f'\n🏆 MOST LIKELY BIRTH DATE: {most_likely_date[0]} (from {most_likely_date[1]} reliable sources)') else: print('❌ No reliable sources found with birth information') #
